An first pass at a revamped Wicket examples This commit introduces an experimental module for a new, revitalizedWicket Examples project.The Wicket Examples project borrows heavily from Twitter's bootstrapdocumentation pages, as they are currently the golden standard fordocumentation and examples.The styling and functionality is a 1-1 copy of Bootstrap. This willbe themed to a new Wicket style as the new Wicket web site will takeshape.The experimental modules also recieve a new module: Bootstrap. Thiswill be the integration point for Twitter's bootstrap CSS and JSplatform into Wicket. I'm still looking at l0rdn1kk0n's bootstrapintegration at github https://github.com/l0rdn1kk0n/wicket-bootstrapand to develop that further in this module. Currently ourintegration only contains the Bootstrap 2.0.3 resources.
